[[Cast a fire spell|Disruption]]
[[Wait|Blunder(Prep)]] 


:: Backstory {"position":"900,300","size":"100,100"}
On a cold winter night, deep in the Appalachian mountains, a pained howl emerges from the woods. Young Silas is awoken with a start, and runs to his father's room. By the time he gets there, his father is already up, unracking his gun.

"What was that, Dad?" Silas asks, trembling in fear.

"Nothing, son. Get your sister, and hide in the basement. I'll be right there, okay?"

"But Dad-!"

"NOW!'

Shaking off his tiredness, Silas gets a closer look at his father. Though his face shows unwavering confidence, his hands are shaking like trees in a hurricane. 

"...Okay. But, promise you'll come quick?"

"Of course, son. Now go!"

[[Hide|Backstory II]]


:: Backstory II {"position":"900,500","size":"100,100"}
Wasting no time, Silas gets his sister, and runs to the basement. Quaking in fear, he waits for his parents. After a few minutes, he hears gunshots, followed by two bloodcurdling screams. Both children start crying, and Silas desperately hopes his father will come through that door any second to calm them down. However, he knows what those screams most likely mean, and moves to barricade the door.

Just a moment too late.

Big claws the size of bowie knives tear through the flimsy wood, and the whole door begins to splinter. Silas dives under a couch and silences his breathing. He screams for his sister to follow him, but she freezes in the middle of the basement. Realizing it's too late, Silas bites back sobs as he watches his sister be ripped apart. The monster scurries from the basement upstairs. Silas comes out to see the aftermath. The pool of blood coats the left side of his face, and her screams will haunt Silas to his last day.

[[Present Day]]


