:: Cautious(Inv) {"position":"550,1700","size":"100,100"}
In a room far away, two men sit at a table.

"So, he didn't take the bait, huh?" The first man says.

"He must have noticed our barrier stones. We put some powerful cloaking spells on those, he must be quite powerful to have noticed them. We must be careful, Valeris." The second man responds.

"It's quite a shame, Nalen. A man of his skill would do great work in the Orda, yet he seems to have settled for being a mere vigilante. Why?" Valeris ponders.

"No matter. If he's this cautious, we must be far more subtle in our approach. Perhaps he recognized our bait wasn't native to this environment?"

"Perhaps. Whatever it is, he's clearly a bigger threat to the balance of our world than we had assumed. A rogue hunter with that kind of magical ability cannot be ignored."

"We need more intel. We should follow him around, learn what makes him tick. If we can fabricate a call he can't ignore, we'll have him for sure!" Nalen proclaims, a goofy smile on his face.

[["Agreed"|Next Hunt(Cautious)]]


