:: Orda Exposed {"position":"1100,3300","size":"100,100"}
Your intense battle with Nalen attracts nearby monster hunters towards your location. Their identities becomes exposed. 

//"ITS THOSE ELVEN PROTECTORS, KILL THEM."// A monster hunter yelled.

The group of monster hunters start charging towards Valeris and Nalen. "Nalen, we must flee //NOW.//" The elven protectors start to flee the scene away from the group. You lower your guard as they run away and conversate with the other monster hunters. 

"What are you doing out here fighting these elven protectors son?" A monster hunter said. 

"They was attacking me sir! I was fighting for me dear life trying to hold on. The stories were all lies. They are traitors to humans!" you exclaimed. 

"What are you saying son? You are speaking nonsense." Another monster hunter said. 

"Believe me, I didn't believe it at first. These elven protectors, the Orda, they want humans killed. You need to believe me, they were going to //kill// me if you guys didn't come sooner. We must alert the public about this. We must declare war on the Orda Aldressia." you said, smirking with a grin. 

"You speak nonsense son. You are to be put away and revoked of your license effective immediately." Another monster hunter said. 

"WHAT! On what grounds?"

"For disrupting the peace and causing havoc in this forest. You realize that when hunting monsters, we keep damage to a minimum and you did not follow that at all. Come on, let's go."

You are cuffed on the spot and get sent away for your supposed crimes. You can't help but realize you can't continue your mission anymore. It seems this battle has resulted in a [[tie.|End Game/Credits]] 


:: Present Day {"position":"900,700","size":"100,100"}
"Thanks for the tip, Barb! I'll have it dealt with before dawn hits your window!" Silas says, standing up from his seat at the diner.

"Oh, thank you! Glad we can always rely on our local monster hunter!"

As Silas walks out the door, his friendly smile hardens into cold concentration. "//Great, another monster just on the outskirts of town. That's the tenth monster sighting this week! Not to mention there being a damn gnoll in the forest! Gnolls live in savannas, how did it even get here?!//" Silas thinks to himself, making his way home. "//Whatever. Nothing I can't handle. I'll just grab my gear, get to the scene, dispatch it and be home for dinner!//"

